SIMPLE: periscopic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Periscopic
<hw>Per`i*scop"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>p⟦eacute⟧riscopique</ets>.]</ety> <def>Viewing all around, or on
all sides.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>of or relating to a periscope{2}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Periscopic spectacles</b></col> <fld>(Opt.)</fld>,
<cd>spectacles having concavo-convex or convexo-concave lenses with a
considerable curvature corresponding to that of the eye, to increase the
distinctness of objects viewed obliquely.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perish</ent>⟦br⟧
